@bojan no change, sspend light keeps blinking, fan spins up a bit and I have to
long-press the power button. On resume /sys/power/disk is back on platform.  BTW
also on 1-200, 1-201 hasn't popped up on yum yet.

@bojan: Forgot about /etc/systemd/sleep.conf :shame: systemd was defaulting back
to platform.  Setting HibernateMode=shutdown there I have full hibernate again.
If this persists in -201 or .2 I'll open a bug.
